build-hardware\" target=\"_blank\">If you can use open source, you can build hardware</a></li>\n\t<li>Read pg. 4 in this report, including the diagram:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www2.deloitte.com/content/dam/insights/us/articles/manufacturing-ecosystems-exploring-world-connected-enterprises/DUP_2898_Industry4.0ManufacturingEcosystems.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Industry 4.0 and manufacturing ecosystems</a></li>\n\t<li>Read or skim this article on the <a href=\"https://excelpro.ca/en/news/the-automation-pyramid-isa-95\" target=\"_blank\">ISA95 Pyramid</a></li>\n\t<li>Differences between PLCs (Programmable Logic Controllers) and SBCs (Single Board Computers): read the <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/PLC/comments/2a5g4q/comment/ciry1u2/\" target=\"_blank\">first&nbsp;comment&nbsp;on this reddit thread</a></li>\n\t<li>Skim the first 4 (short!) sections of this doc on Ladder Logic (LL): <a href=\"https://www.solisplc.com/tutorials/how-to-read-ladder-logic\" target=\"_blank\">how to read ladder logic​​​​​​</a>\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>No need to read the &quot;Advanced Circuit Branching Ladder Logic Practice&quot; section or below.</li>\n\t\t<li>Consider that LL may be more intuitive for a technician on a factory floor, but typically LL&nbsp;(and other industrial programming) lacks version control, unit testing, and other infrastructure that supports modern software.</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n"],"question":"text only","notes":" notes ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSource":" ","multimediaTitle":" ","multimedia":"http://res.cloudinary.com/terra-do/image/upload/v1691785524/Events/p0wljys6f6wx2sx77zbc.jpg","slideType":"information","version":4,"editor":"jaime@terra.do","hints":[""]},{"classId":"software-for-climate-5","slideId":"4","questionType":"media+text","slideTemplateId":"L1","slideHeading":"Conclusion","body":["<div>See you in the live session!</div>\n"],"question":" ","notes":" ","multimediaType":"image","multimediaSource":" ","multimediaTitle":" ","multimedia":"http: